New sponsors of the popular quiz show, Who Wants To Be A Millionaire, have explained why the reality show has returned to Nigerian television screens. The sponsors, UP, Payattitude, Payarena, and HopePSBank stated that the rebirth of the family show is geared towards building a better future for Nigeria.   Oxford University gets first Igbo language lecturer     Wife stabs senior rival to death in Ondo     Burna Boy’s elated grandma praises singer over bag gift   According to the Managing Director of UP,  Agada Apochi, the group’s decision to sponsor Who Wants To Be A Millionaire? Series 2-The Rebirth’ was borne out of the desire to inform, educate, and entertain Nigerians by bringing back the game show that keeps families at the edge of their seats. “Entertainment brings people together, whether it is football or show. It brings families together colleagues together. It is for that reason we are investing in entertainment. For that reason, we are bringing back Who Wants To Be A Millionaire? “For us in the UP group, we should invest in this TV game show not only because we want to promote our brands but also because we want to see a better Nigeria. You would agree with me there is no better way to build a better future for Nigeria than investment in education”, he said. SPONSORED